# Shared Packages

## Overview

Three shared packages provide foundation functionality across the monorepo.

---

## c3-ui: UI Component Library

**Path**: `packages/ui`
**Package**: `@acme/ui`
**Type**: Foundation (React components)

### Exports

| Component | Props | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `Button` | `children`, `variant?`, `onClick?` | Action button with primary/secondary variants |
| `Card` | `children`, `title?` | Container with optional title |
| `Input` | `placeholder?`, `type?`, `value?`, `onChange?` | Form input field |

### Button Component
```typescript
interface ButtonProps {
  children: ReactNode;
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
  onClick?: () => void;
}
```

### Card Component
```typescript
interface CardProps {
  children: ReactNode;
  title?: string;
}
```

### Input Component
```typescript
interface InputProps {
  placeholder?: string;
  type?: "text" | "email" | "password";
  value?: string;
  onChange?: (value: string) => void;
}
```

### Usage
```tsx
import { Button, Card, Input } from "@acme/ui";
```

---

## c3-api-client: API Client

**Path**: `packages/api-client`
**Package**: `@acme/api-client`
**Type**: Foundation (HTTP client)

### Configuration
- `API_URL` environment variable (default: `http://localhost:3001`)

### Exports

```typescript
export const api = {
  products: {
    list(): Promise<Product[]>,
    get(id: string): Promise<Product>,
  },
  orders: {
    create(items: OrderItem[]): Promise<Order>,
  },
};
```

### Usage
```typescript
import { api } from "@acme/api-client";

const products = await api.products.list();
const order = await api.orders.create([{ productId: "1", quantity: 2 }]);
```

---

## c3-database: Database Client

**Path**: `packages/database`
**Package**: `@acme/database`
**Type**: Foundation (Data access)

### Note
Currently a mock implementation. In production, would wrap Prisma or similar ORM.

### Exports

```typescript
export const db = {
  product: {
    findMany(): Promise<Product[]>,
    findUnique({ where: { id } }): Promise<Product>,
  },
  order: {
    create({ data }): Promise<Order>,
  },
};
```

### Usage
```typescript
import { db } from "@acme/database";

const products = await db.product.findMany();
const order = await db.order.create({ data: { items } });
```

---

## Dependency Graph

```
@acme/web
    ├── @acme/ui
    └── @acme/api-client

@acme/api
    └── @acme/database
```

